      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALWAYSBJOY NZ (4) is a progressive filly who has put two wins together at this circuit and distance, one of them from this barrier when scoring by close to 10m. Has the speed to push forward and is a big chance to land the hat trick. NITRATOR (6) completed a hat trick when resuming with a win by 6 metres at this circuit and distance. Draws wider but should strip fitter so could continue his charge. SWEET DIOR NZ (7) draws wide but is in form, winning at this circuit and distance first up before placing from the back row last time. Suited back to this trip having won two of her three attempts. WILPEKA (3) was a beaten favourite from a tough barrier last start but is progressive having yet to miss a place and is much better served by this draw.",
